result.text:
🍵Tea is a way of life for Chinese people. Experience the essence of life through the traditional tea ceremony of the Bai ethnic group - San Dao Cha (Chinese: 三道茶), or three-course tea, a ritual to welcome guests🤗.

The first course is called "bitter tea". The tea leaves are roasted, and when the aroma fills the air, boiling water is added. The second course is called "sweet tea". It is made by adding a kind of milk cheese known as dairy fan🥛, along with licorice, walnuts, and brown sugar. The third course is called "aftertaste tea". It is made by steeping tea with honey, Sichuan pepper, and ginger, creating a blend of bitter, sweet, and spicy flavors. The wisdom and philosophy found in the tea ceremony are captivating, offering a unique perspective on life.

It is cherished as a national-level intangible cultural heritage in China, and as part of the "Traditional Chinese Tea-making Techniques and Related Customs", it is also listed in the Representative List of the Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity by UNESCO🤩. #Chineseway #ChineseTea @goyunnanchina @Amazing_Yunnan @WondersYunnan
